    "The Augustinian monastery is an important pilgrimage station on the Way of St. James. It was renovated a few years ago and now offers many pilgrims good overnight accommodation.",
    "The itinerary through the forest is a very simple and at the same time very picturesque walk. A forest track with sections of trails that meanders between beech and oak trees and beautiful meadows, finally connecting with a section of the Camino de Santiago. Its name refers to Basajaun, the \"lord of the forest\" in Basque mythology."
